#### 🧮 Calculations

The previous step stored all the data we will need in the dataframe. Quantities added later can be derived from existing data.

  - Add a column `N` with values equal to the sum of `S`, `I`, and `R`, then add a column `R0` calculating the ratio of `beta` to `gamma`.

  - The epidemic started on January 1, 2020. Create a `date` column giving the day associated with each data row, then set this column as the index (instead of the integer we used previously).

    📖 : [`datetime64`](https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/arrays.datetime.html) (NumPy),
    [`daterange`](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.date_range.html),
    [`DataFrame.set_index`](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.set_index.html) (pandas)

  - Calculate the number of new infections $\beta I S/N$ per day and define a new column `T` counting the total number of infections since the start of the epidemic.

    📖 : [`DataFrame.eval`](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.eval.html), [`Dataframe.cumsum`](https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/reference/api/pandas.DataFrame.cumsum.html) (pandas)

<Admonition type="solution" open={false}>
</summary>
```python
df["N"] = df["S"] + df["I"] + df["R"]
df["R0"] = df["beta"] / df["gamma"]
```

